# Cursor Project Rules

- Use `AGENTS.md` as the default source of truth.
- Do not auto-resume Betelgeuze/Codex goal state for ordinary edits.
- Do not inspect `.betelgeuze/`, worker raw logs, or productization evidence unless the user explicitly requests readiness/gap-closure work.
- For delegated implementation, keep prompt files short and use the wrappers in `docs/ai/ORCHESTRATION.md`.
- Treat 50+ LOC, 3+ files, broad search, repeated test-fix loops, or long evidence diagnosis as worker candidates.
- Do not run push/deploy/publish/release/migration/payment/cloud/permission-escalation commands without human approval.
- Do not read or print `.env`, `.env.*`, `*.env`, or `*.env.*`.
- Report changed files, tests, failed tests, core diff summary, and blockers.
